fields.description:
It was found during investigation of EUCA-4735 that the cluster controller takes over 60 seconds to respond to an address unassignment in some situations.

To reproduce the issue you can run an instance and terminate as soon as it enters the running state:

{code}
# euca-run-instances emi-XXXXXXXX; for N in {1..1000}; do ID=$(euca-describe-instances --filter instance-state-name=running | grep INSTANCE | awk '{print $2}'); if [ ! -z "$ID" ] ; then euca-terminate-instances $ID; fi; sleep 0.05; done
{code}

The read timeout on the cloud controller is 60 seconds by default so this is causing a failure / rollback.
